      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C (140°C fan). Put a large casserole pan over a medium-high heat with a good glug of olive oil.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Pat the lamb dry, season with salt and pepper, and brown in the pan in two batches, five minutes a batch until the outside has colour. Lift out to a plate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Drop the heat to medium. Add the onions, carrots, celery, and a pinch of salt. Sweat with the lid on for ten minutes, stirring occasionally, until soft and starting to go translucent.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir in the garlic, rosemary, thyme, cumin, and smoked paprika. Cook for one minute, the spices should bloom into the oil.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Pour in the red wine and let it bubble down for two minutes, scraping the base of the pan.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Return the lamb. Add the lemon zest and juice, the chickpeas, the tomatoes, and the stock. Bring to a simmer.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lid on, into the oven for two and a half to three hours. The meat is ready when it pulls apart easily under a fork.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir in the potatoes thirty-five minutes before serving so they cook through in the sauce.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Taste and adjust the seasoning. Lift the lid for the last fifteen minutes if you want the sauce a bit thicker.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Scatter with the chopped parsley and serve with bread to mop up the sauce.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish.",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking, food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one, gentler than full blast.",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegetarian swap: replace meat with mushrooms, lentils, or beans, adjust seasoning to compensate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Spice version: a pinch of chilli flakes or cracked black pepper at the end shifts the dish without losing its character.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
